result.notes:
The fishing vessels *Hollie J* and *Magdalene Ann* were chartered in June 
2006 to carry out a potting survey for velvet crabs in the area from 
Flamborough Head to North of Spurn Point (Bridlington Bay, North Sea, UK) as 
part of the Fisheries Science Partnership programme 2006/07. The primary 
objective was to plot the spatial distribution of catch rates of macro 
crustaceans in the mixed fishery of Bridlington bay. Data are the numbers of 
crustacea ( *Necora puber, Cancer pagurus and Homarus gammarus* ) by trap 
and size distributions of velvet crabs ( *Necora Puber* ).
